    • Method Detail

      • inputPaths

        public Set<Path> inputPaths()
        An immutable copy of input paths that contains the data of this Dataset to be compacted.

      • inputLatePaths

        public Set<Path> inputLatePaths()
        An immutable copy of paths that contains the late data of this Dataset to be compacted. Late input data may be generated if the input data is obtained from another compaction, e.g., if we run hourly compaction and daily compaction on a topic where the compacted hourly data is the input to the daily compaction. If this path contains any data and this Dataset is not already compacted, deduplication will be applied to this Dataset.

      • outputPath

        public Path outputPath()
        Output path for the compacted data.

      • outputLatePath

        public Path outputLatePath()
        If outputPath() is already compacted and new input data is found, those data can be copied to this path.

      • outputTmpPath

        public Path outputTmpPath()
        The path where the MR job writes output to. Data will be published to outputPath() if the compaction is successful.
